netInt.graphElements

Class GraphElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • netInt.graphElements.GraphElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Edge, Node

    public abstract class GraphElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Abstract class that handles two collections for storage of graphElements' attributes (either nodes or edges). The first collection contains absolute attributes, i.e., raw attributes independent of any graph processing, e.g, the amount sent by one payer to one beneficiary is the weight of an edge linking their nodes. The second set are relative attributes, i.e., attributes that get values from graph processing. An example of the latter is node degree after clustering. A node has a relative degree inside each cluster to which it belongs. For convenience, node and edge graph metrics (inDegree, outDegree, degree) are stored in the collection of relative attributes in numbered sequence, reserving 0 for the root graph.
    Author:
    jsalam

      • setCommunity

        public void setCommunity(java.lang.String community,
                         int key)
        Parameters:
        community - the community name to which the node belongs
        key - the metadata level associated to the community. This means that some statistics of the node such as betweenness or degree are relative to the community to which it belongs. If the node belongs to more than one community, then the key identifies the community to which the attributes are associated. 0 is reserved for the root community
